      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's exactly what i'm talking about. why did they suggest those readings weren't worth investigating if they were actually part of the mission? it feels less like a \"mistake\" and more like a deliberate way to downplay the significance of what was seen. if there were actual structures or something artificial there, wouldn't the government have a massive reason to spin it as just \"unexplained anomalies\" to prevent a global panic or a total shift in how we see our place in the universe? what kind of specific data points do you think would be most likely to be redacted from the official mission logs to keep that kind of thing quiet?",
